Kebbi State Commissioner for Local Governments and Chieftaincy Affairs, Alhaji Muhammad Shalla, said the state government has procured 65,000 bags of foodstuff worth N580 million to be  distributed across the state. The distribution is being handled by an NGO, Khadimiyya for Justice and Development. Shalla made this known to reporters in Birnin Kebbi at the weekend. The gesture, he said, was to ease the difficulty during Ramadan.   ‘NASFAT should deepen youth education’     How Nigeria can be great, by Popoola     Village Head, 14 others killed in Kaduna attacks   He said: “As part of Governor Atiku Bagudu-led administration’s effort to cushion the effect of difficulties and challenges face by the people, especially in rural areas, the state government has procured 65,000 bags of foodstuff worth N580 million to be distributed across the state.” He hailed the NGO for distributing more than 17,000 bags of parboiled rice to 21 local government areas of the state for onward distribution to the less- privileged. The commissioner called on well-to- do individuals in the state to emulate the NGO Secretary to the State Government, Alhaji Babale Umar-Yauri, who represented Governor Atiku Bagudu, said the administration had been providing assistance to people across the state since inception in 2015. “More than 30,000 bags of assorted food items have been procured by the state government for distribution to people as part of efforts bring down prices of food items in the state.’